item.title: Words
item.dc:creator: @sk8rdude461 sk8rdude461
item.description:
@sk8rdude461 wrote:

popcorn57:

Is that like in your quest tab? because that type of stuff is in my PlayerAssistant.java just search in that folder and look for some of those words and should find it. hope this helps

File search would search all open projects for a matching string.
[hr]

OP: You can try similar to this to try and find the ID of the interface, and then search that in file search. If no results, just use packet 126 to change the text server sided.

[quote=“sk8rdude461, post:8, topic:550451”]To answer your first question:
Make a command to clear all interface text and set them as their IDs.
Note: You will need to restart your client after your finished. Also, the command will take a while to “process” and the client will seem frozen. Let it do it’s thing.

if(playerCommand.equalsIgnoreCase("clear")) { for(int i = 0; i < 30000; i++) { c.getPA().sendFrame126(Integer.toString(i), i); } }

Then use the command and look at the achievement tab.
In a few moments, once the command is done executing, you’ll see all the ID’s.[/quote]
The code was for a 317 PI, you may have to make some changes.
